        "option_c_result": "INCORRECT - Issuing an RFI to external agencies is a procurement activity, typically part of the Planning or Executing process groups, and implies a decision to potentially outsource. It is premature during Initiating, especially without first assessing internal capabilities or a more concrete understanding of specific resource gaps. This step should only be taken once internal options are exhausted or deemed insufficient.",
        "option_d_result": "INCORRECT - Interviewing potential team members is part of the Acquire Resources process, but it's typically done once roles are defined and resource requirements are clearer, which happens more in Planning or Executing. During Initiating, the focus is on a high-level understanding of resource needs and availability, not individual selection. Jumping to interviews without a clear plan can lead to misallocations and misunderstandings.",
